# Sequence 01 — PM's Slack message → merged PR (PRD §6.1)

The end-to-end happy path: a PM drops a one-paragraph feature idea in Slack, the platform runs it through all seven stages with real human-approval gates, and the result is a merged PR. Every step has an owner, a gate, a budget, and a log line (PRD §6.1 final sentence).

## Diagram

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor PM as PM (acme-corp)
    actor CTO as CTO (acme-corp)
    participant Slack as Slack MCP
    participant Orch as Master Orchestrator
    participant IdB as Identity Broker
    participant IdP as acme IdP (OIDC)
    participant BA as BA agent (ideation)
    participant Arch as Architect agent
    participant Dev as Developer agent
    participant QA as QA agent
    participant Sec as Security agent
    participant DevOps as DevOps agent
    participant Docs as Docs agent
    participant Bus as NATS + event-bus-bridge
    participant Audit as Audit Account (SQS + S3)

    PM->>Slack: "Add SSO via Okta to acme/app"
    Slack->>Orch: webhook (Slack MCP, plan-then-act validated)
    Orch->>IdB: resolve tenant_id from channel mapping
    IdB-->>Orch: tenant_id=acme-corp
    Orch->>Orch: CreateRun(goal, project, trigger={kind:slack,actor:pm@acme})
    Orch->>Bus: publish run.created
    Bus->>Audit: ship audit row
    Orch-->>BA: wake (stage=ideation)

    BA->>Orch: GetRunContext (gRPC)
    Orch-->>BA: RunContext{stage=ideation, allow_list=ideation, ...}
    BA->>BA: emit Plan{tool_calls: [slack.read_thread, jira.create_epic, ...]}
    BA->>Orch: AdvanceStage(decision=NEXT, artefact=draft_prd)
    Orch->>Bus: publish gate.requested (ideation->architect, approver=ceo)
    Bus->>Audit: ship audit row
    Orch-->>CEO: request_confirmation(prompt="Approve draft PRD?")

    CTO->>Orch: POST /v1/approvals/{id}/decisions {decision: accept}
    Orch->>Orch: stage=architect, run.status=running
    Orch-->>Arch: wake (stage=architect)
    Arch->>Orch: AdvanceStage(decision=NEXT, artefact=adr-0011+hld+lld)
    Orch->>Bus: publish gate.requested (architect->dev, approver=cto)

    CTO->>Orch: POST /v1/approvals/{id}/decisions {decision: accept}
    Orch-->>Dev: wake (stage=dev)
    Dev->>Dev: Plan{tool_calls: [github.create_branch, code.write, github.open_pr]}
    Dev->>Orch: AdvanceStage(decision=NEXT, artefact=pr_url)
    Orch-->>QA: wake (stage=qa)

    QA->>QA: integration + e2e + perf baseline
    QA->>Orch: AdvanceStage(decision=NEXT, artefact=qa_verdict=pass)
    Orch-->>Sec: wake (stage=security)
    Sec->>Sec: OWASP scan, threat model, SBOM
    Sec->>Orch: AdvanceStage(decision=NEXT, artefact=security_verdict=pass)
    Orch-->>DevOps: wake (stage=devops)

    DevOps->>DevOps: Terraform plan, Helm chart, ArgoCD app
    DevOps->>Orch: AdvanceStage(decision=NEXT, artefact=deploy_plan)
    Orch->>Bus: publish gate.requested (devops->docs, approver=ceo+cto)
    CTO->>Orch: POST /v1/approvals/{id}/decisions {decision: accept}
    Orch-->>Docs: wake (stage=docs)
    Docs->>Docs: README, API ref, CHANGELOG, Confluence
    Docs->>Orch: AdvanceStage(decision=NEXT, artefact=confluence_url)
    Orch->>Orch: run.status=done, run.current_stage=done
    Orch->>Bus: publish run.finished
    Bus->>Audit: ship final audit row
    Orch-->>PM: Slack notification (thread reply)

    Note over Orch,Audit: Every action above is one audit_log row. Total: ~28 rows for this run. ~$3.20 in model spend (median PRD §8 budget).
```

## Notes

- **Gates 1, 2, 7 are human-in-the-loop.** Gates 3, 4, 5, 6 are typed but auto-approved by the orchestrator when the stage emits a passing verdict; the CTO can still pause.
- **Plan-then-act (ADR-0005)** runs on every agent invocation. Destructive tools (force-push, drop DB, post to a customer channel) carry `requires_approval: true` and pause the run.
- **Idempotency-Key (ADR-0004)** is on every Orchestrator mutating call. A retry of any step is a no-op.
- **Audit row count** is a proxy for cost — the Eval agent's dashboards expose per-stage token + USD so the Cost agent can flag overruns before the run finishes.
- **Failure mode** at any gate: the agent returns `decision: RETURN` and the run loops back to the prior stage. A budget breach pauses the run and surfaces a "budget exceeded" state.
